text: Antonovka () is a rural locality (a village) and the administrative center of Shevchenkovsky Selsoviet, Meleuzovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 443 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 15 km from Meleuz. == References == Category:Rural localities in Meleuzovsky District
title: Antonovka, Meleuzovsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
